Devolution CAS Hussein Dado’s son Dado Gamada tied the knot over the weekend in a big-budget traditional Orma wedding in Oda Garsen constituency, Tana River county. Gamada, a pilot, moved away from the luxurious lifestyle and went back to the traditional roots to marry the love of his life, Asha Abdulrahman. His young brother Galgalo Hussein also signed a contract of marriage (Nikah) with his fiancé Gamar Abdulrahman. Present were Devolution CS Eugene Wamalwa, PS Charles Sunkuli and former Tana River woman representative Halima Warre.